@Francis

Turns out it's pretty archaic and from the 18th century.

(And that I should just look stuff up before I post pointless questions here...)

@Matt
I learned ADNOUN through studying old journalism and linguistic papers from the time of the American Revolution (ill-fated idea of contributing to Colonial Williamsburg academic research…I quickly exceeded my limitations). It appears to have been in use sometime in the late 1700s and faded away not too long afterward. Today, it is considered archaic. 

So, unless your grammar classes were a few hundred years ago, you probably never saw that word in class. We called adjectives used as nouns, “nouns.”

